  [
    {
      "id": "outputNameTemplateNote",
      "type": "LabelInput",
      "title": "",
      "mode": "output",
      "props": {
        "content": "<div class='space-y-1 text-xs text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed'><div>Build output names with <code class='rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] font-mono'>{token}</code> placeholders. Tokens are lowercased before matching.</div><ul class='list-disc pl-4 space-y-1'><li><code class='rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] font-mono'>{filename}</code> keeps the original file name.</li><li>Core metadata tokens map to the original audio tags, for example <code class='rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] font-mono'>{album}</code>, <code class='rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] font-mono'>{album_artist}</code>, <code class='rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] font-mono'>{title}</code>, <code class='rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] font-mono'>{track}</code>, <code class='rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] font-mono'>{disc}</code>.</li><li>Unknown tokens stay as literal text, so you can mix static text freely.</li></ul><div>Example: <code class='rounded bg-muted px-1 py-0.5 text-[12px] font-mono'>{artist}-{album}-{track}</code></div></div>",
        "autoHeight": true
      }
    }
  ],
